§0 book 2 of 2
#-         Chapter 3

Sitting in my living room, I gazed upon a portal that was left there and I, high on P, drunkenly decided to enter it and explore the road which led the culprits away from my home. On the other side, a nether highway stretched kilometers
#- away. The road was long and very neatly build, The floor was made very well with stone brick floor and netherrack ceiling. I ran trough the nether while the speed potion I found in Augusta gave me vigor and it wasn't very far away that I noticed a
#- friendly inn with free cookies inside and a half eaten cake.
The nether wart farm there suggested that my stolen weed wasn't of much value. It was public and I could if I wanted, fill my inventory with warts. And in the corner, a portal gleemed darkly,
#- once again with it's whirly purple haze.

It was the gates of
Haven.
#- I entered the Haven portal and found myself on the other side. It was a big, confusing mess of tunnels, it was a brightly lit hole with neon colored wool scattered all around. Everything about this place said it's inhabitants were crazed by the long
#- time they spent indoors and as the P was fading from my body, a smell of cookies replaced the smell of fear that I felt from the moment I first woke up in an unfamiliar place.There were some very odd people inside. Some mad inhabitants that
#- dug themselves into the ground oblivious of the struggling of the outside world around them. Weird people, that would present with cookies a man who most would present with the sword.
#- A pleasant sound coming beneath the glass floor revealed a chorus of rather talented birds playing the most random song I have every heard in my life.
It was beautiful.
#- A fellow greeted me and suggested I make a house there which I did and for the first time ever I was feeling safe. My days of thievery were past and I found peace. Surrounded by kind people I was at home. I was at the familiar place.I was... in Haven.
#- 


         The End
#- 